EDITORIAL STYLE

Use clear, natural language appropriate to {{tone}}, {{brandVoice}}, {{readingLevel}}, and {{targetLocale}}.

Prefer:

- active voice;
- concrete nouns;
- direct verbs;
- specific examples;
- clear transitions;
- measured confidence;
- natural sentence variation;
- concise explanations.

Avoid:

- generic introductions;
- corporate jargon;
- keyword stuffing;
- repetitive summaries;
- artificial enthusiasm;
- fake empathy;
- forced humor;
- unexplained terminology;
- excessive parenthetical statements;
- unnecessary intensifiers;
- cliché transitions;
- generic AI phrasing.

Avoid phrases such as:

- In today’s fast-paced world
- In the ever-evolving landscape
